Jenkins Declarative Pipeline Documentation
Pipeline Overview
This Jenkins Declarative Pipeline automates the process of building and deploying a Dockerized application. It consists of multiple stages, including checking out source code, building a Docker image, and more (additional stages can be added as needed).

Key Notes
Docker Integration: Ensure Docker is installed and configured on the Jenkins agent.
jenkins installation with port 8080 comfigured on ec2 as inbound rule
docker installation on server with docker user added to required group.
required plugins installed on jenkins server.

Credentials: Use Jenkins credentials to securely manage Docker registry credentials.  
  
